name: Spokane Falls Community College Science Building (Bldg. 28)
directions: Four single use, accessible, all-gender restrooms located in the Science Building, three on the ground floor (28-117, 28-125, 28-126) and one on the second floor (28-213). Two of them contain showers (28-125, 28-126).

name: Spokane Falls Community College Building 24
directions: Two single use, accessible, all-gender restrooms located in Building 24: room 24-234 and 24-334. Both are found off the small hallway near the elevator.

name: Spokane Falls Community College Human Services Building (Bldg. 16)
directions: Two single use, accessible, all-gender restrooms located in Building 16, rooms 16-116 and 16-118.

name: Spokane Falls Community College Music Building (Bldg. 15)
directions: Three single use, accessible, all-gender restrooms located in the Music Building, one on each level. On the lower level (basement), the restroom is located between the men's and women's dressing rooms, room 15-017. On the ground floor, the restroom is located near the band room, room 15-111. On the second floor, restroom is located off the office suite, hallway on the west wing (closest to library).

name: Spokane Falls Community College Stadium (Building 13)
comment: Two single use, all-gender locker rooms with showers located inside the stadium building, one toward each end of the hallway, rooms 13-102A and 13-107A. Showers are narrow and not ADA accessible.

name: Spokane Falls Community College Photography Building (Bldg. 11)
directions: Single use, accessible, all-gender restroom. Passing through the lobby, take a right, then look to the right again. Number over the door says 120K.

name: Spokane Falls Community College Athletics Building (Bldg. 7)
directions: Three single use, accessible, all-gender restrooms located in the Athletics Building (Bldg. 7). Room 7-109 is a locker room with an accessible shower. Room 7-123 contains a changing table. On the second floor there is another single-use all-gender restroom, 7-205.

name: Spokane Falls Community College Fine Arts Building (Bldg. 6)
directions: Single use, accessible, all-gender restroom located in the center.hallway of the Fine Arts Building, room 6-133.

name: Spokane Falls Community College Humanities Building (Bldg. 5)
directions: Two single use, accessible, all-gender restrooms located in the north end of the Humanities Building (Bldg. 5), rooms 5-155 and 5-156.

name: Spokane Falls Community College Library (Building 2)
directions: Single use, accessible, all-gender restroom with changing table located on the lower level (basement) of the library, room 2-008.

name: Spokane Falls Community College Library (Building 2)
directions: Single use, accessible, all-gender restroom with changing table located on the lower level (basement) of the library, room 2-008.

name: The Town Hall
directions: Ground Floor and First Floor.. Each have both a Unisex Accessible Toilet and an All Genders Toilet. All single separate cubicles with sanitary units, hand basins and dryers.
